WEBVTT

00:02.534 --> 00:04.534
Which brings us to 2005...

00:04.835 --> 00:07.135
The Circle Park renovation was complete,

00:07.436 --> 00:10.136
and a young man
named Thomas Haverford

00:10.237 --> 00:12.305
was still two years away
from getting hired.

00:12.373 --> 00:15.241
Perhaps we could skip ahead
and just hit the highlights?

00:15.309 --> 00:17.610
I mean, I planned
a comprehensive retrospective,

00:17.678 --> 00:19.779
but I guess I can just focus
on the really important moments.

00:19.847 --> 00:22.982
Ah! The debate about getting
a pod-based coffee machine.

00:23.050 --> 00:25.818
Garry and I wrote a little
musical number about that,

00:25.886 --> 00:28.388
and it goes a little something
like thi--

00:28.455 --> 00:29.855
Can't we just quickly
shake hands,

00:29.890 --> 00:31.024
pretend we like each other,

00:31.091 --> 00:32.570
- and get out of here?
- I'm all for that.

00:32.593 --> 00:35.061
No, April, Ron,
we need to celebrate everything

00:35.129 --> 00:36.596
that we've done together
as a group.

00:36.663 --> 00:38.197
This is our last day here!

00:38.265 --> 00:41.267
Who knows when we'll all be
together like this again?

00:41.335 --> 00:42.702
Excuse me.
Hi.

00:42.770 --> 00:44.103
There's a swing in a park

00:44.171 --> 00:46.472
near my house that's been broken
for about three months.

00:46.540 --> 00:48.241
Is it possible
to get that fixed?

00:48.309 --> 00:52.145
Anything is possible
if you follow your dreams.

00:52.213 --> 00:53.313
Johnny Karate.

00:53.380 --> 00:55.115
Except getting a swing fixed.

00:55.232 --> 00:56.712
None of us
actually work here anymore.

00:56.767 --> 00:58.635
Come back in two hours
when the office is open.

00:58.703 --> 01:00.770
- Thank you.
- Wait.

01:00.838 --> 01:03.340
Actually, sir, we can help.

01:03.407 --> 01:06.676
We can and we will because
when we used to work here,

01:06.744 --> 01:08.478
helping people was our job.

01:08.546 --> 01:09.879
Forget about these old stories.

01:09.947 --> 01:11.081
Let's make a new one.

01:11.148 --> 01:12.716
Let's fix a swing.

01:12.783 --> 01:14.384
One last ride
for the Parks and Rec gang.

01:14.452 --> 01:15.452
Who's in?

01:15.453 --> 01:16.620
All: Yeah.

01:16.687 --> 01:18.655
♪ The vote
was four to three ♪

01:18.723 --> 01:20.457
♪ Donna said to get rid of me

01:20.524 --> 01:21.925
♪ But Ron was suspicious

01:21.993 --> 01:24.060
♪ 'Cause my coffee
was delicious ♪

01:24.078 --> 01:26.079
Come on, Garry,
you're the mayor now.

01:26.147 --> 01:28.648
Have some dignity.

01:28.716 --> 01:31.651
[Triumphant music]

